pageContext.claim: “There was one protester stood up. And he stood up and he held up a sign, and he said, whatever he said, something. He got more publicity than the speech got...One guy stands up, not an impressive person, he stood up and he got all of this. He took the whole thing away. One person. It wasn't like, gee, we have 25,000 people going crazy.”
pageContext.analysis: It's doubtful Trump only saw a "few" protestors. Local reports noted there were 350 protesters outside Trump's speech, one member of the Virginia House of Delegates heckled the president and the state's Legislative Black Caucus and other Democratic lawmakers boycotted the Jamestown event.
